title.narrative: Enterprise Development through Coastal Resource Management in Camiguin Province, Philippines

description.narrative: Implemented in Camiguin Province, Southern Philippines, this Coastal Resource Management (CRM) project is building capability of communities and local government, through workshops and technical assistance, to manage CRM and take ownership of water monitoring activities, monitoring coral reef and species diversity for Marine Protected Areas and enforcing coastal law. Development of eco-tourism ventures includes establishment funding, enterprise support systems and developing market linkages.
